

India were set a target of 354 to win when South Africa declared their second innings at 265 for eight on the fourth day of the second Test at Kingsmead Friday.

Shaun Pollock made a stroke-filled 63 not out as South Africa pushed for quick runs after lunch. Shanthakumuran Sreesanth was India's most successful bowler with four for 79.

There were 48 overs due to be bowled on the fourth day.

